eNCA senior reporter Aviwe Mtila has more on this story. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Lebogang Monene's family says it hasn't received an apology, or even an acknowledgement, from the family of her ex-lover who allegedly shot her while she was on duty. She is the Tembisa hospital nurse who was gunned down in February. WATCH: Lebogang Monene memorial service The suspect, Lucky Mudau, turned the gun on himself but survived. He's currently a quadriplegic and using a wheelchair. WATCH: Shot and Killed: Who was Lebogang Monene? "As the Monene family, we are still mourning the death of our sister, our daughter. The healing process has not started yet," her brother said. "We were hoping that one day we'll see someone from Mudau's family but that has never happened." "They were the ones who were supposed to come to us and they've never done that."